events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Indiana Pacers guard Tyrese Haliburton cranked up the offense during Friday night's final stretch. Everyone else embraced doing the dirty work on defense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, Haliburton leads Pacers past Trail Blazers 108-99

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine made 11 of 13 3-pointers and scored 41 points and the Chicago Bulls beat Philadelphia 126-112 on Friday night to end the 76ers’ home winning streak at 11.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine hits 11 3s, scores 41 points in Bulls' win over 76ers

events.name: New York Knicks at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 32 points and 11 rebounds, Mitchell Robinson had 10 points and 18 rebounds before fouling out and the New York Knicks won their fourth straight game, beating the Toronto Raptors 112-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks get 1st win in Canada since '15, beat Raptors 112-108

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant and Kyrie Irving combined to miss 32 shots and didn't let it bother them one bit.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant has 33 points to lead Nets past Pelicans, 108-102

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored a season-high 39 points and the Charlotte Hornets matched an NBA record with 51 in the first quarter of a 138-109 rout of the Milwaukee Bucks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, record 1st quarter lead Hornets past Bucks 138-109

events.name: Washington Wizards at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 30 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder completed a regular-season sweep of the Washington Wizards with a 127-110 win on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder complete series sweep of Beal-less Wizards, 127-110

events.name: Detroit Pistons at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Tre Jones had 25 points and the San Antonio Spurs overcame injuries to their two leading scorers to beat the Detroit Pistons 121-109 on Friday night, snapping a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones helps Spurs overcome injuries, Pistons to end skid

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 25 points and 21 rebounds, D’Angelo Russell also scored 25 and the Minnesota Timberwolves cruised to a 128-115 win against the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night.

— Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists, Jamal Murray scored 18 points in his first back-to-back games since knee surgery, and the Denver Nuggets took advantage of Donovan Mitchell's absence to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 121-108 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Murray help Nuggets top Mitchell-less Cavs 121-108

headlines.description: — It wasn't that long ago that Victor Oladipo was an All-Star guard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Oladipo scores 26 points, Heat beat Suns 104-96

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 25 points and 10 assists in his return from an illness, Russell Westbrook added 18 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Atlanta Hawks 130-114 Friday night for their first four-game winning streak...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron leads Lakers past Hawks 130-114 for 4th straight win
